Germany Considering 6% Solar Aid Cut Next Year, Roettgen Says

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   C o m f o r t
-- 
2011-05-30T14:57:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/germany-considering-6-solar-aid-cut-next-year-roettgen-says.html
The German government is considering
a 6 percent reduction in the guaranteed above-market rates paid
to solar power generators next year, Environment Minister
Norbert Roettgen said today at a press conference in Berlin.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Comfort at 
 ncomfort1@bloomberg.net  